---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Our Educational Model - The American Literacy Institute" description="Discover the three pillars of excellence in dyslexia education at The American Literacy Institute.">
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Our Educational Model</h1>
      <p>A paradigm shift in dyslexia education built on three pillars of excellence</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="intro">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="intro-text">
        The American Literacy Institute is not just another private school. It is a paradigm shift in how we
        approach dyslexia education. Our model is built on three pillars of excellence: an unwavering commitment
        to evidence-based instruction, a holistic approach to student development, and a culture of character and faith.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="programs">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="program-card pillar-1">
        <div class="icon-container books">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M4 19.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 17H20"></path>
            <path d="M6.5 2H20v20H6.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2>Pillar 1: Evidence-Based, Multisensory Instruction</h2>
        <p>
          At the core of our academic program is a deep and abiding commitment to the principles of Structured
          Literacy, the gold standard in dyslexia instruction. Our curriculum is fully aligned with the latest
          research in the science of reading and the guidelines of the Texas Dyslexia Handbook.
        </p>
        <h3>Texas-Approved Dyslexia Therapy Programs:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Reading by Design:</strong> A systematic, multisensory program developed by the Region 4 Education Service Center in Texas</li>
          <li><strong>Take Flight:</strong> A comprehensive two-year intervention from the Luke Waites Center for Dyslexia and Learning Disorders</li>
          <li><strong>Neuhaus Basic Language Skills:</strong> Research-based curriculum providing intensive, systematic instruction in reading, spelling, and handwriting</li>
          <li><strong>Wilson Reading System®:</strong> A highly respected program providing structured, sequential, multisensory instruction</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <strong>Intensive & Individualized:</strong> Students receive 60-90 minutes of small-group dyslexia therapy
          each day, with a student-to-teacher ratio of no more than 6:1.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-card pillar-2">
        <div class="icon-container target">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"></circle>
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"></circle>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2>Pillar 2: A Holistic Approach to Student Development</h2>
        <p>
          We believe that a truly great education nurtures the whole child. In addition to our intensive literacy
          instruction, we provide a comprehensive and challenging academic curriculum in all core subjects.
        </p>
        <h3>Comprehensive Curriculum:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Core Academics:</strong> Mathematics, science, and social studies aligned with Texas Essential Knowledge and Skills (TEKS)</li>
          <li><strong>Accessible Design:</strong> Engaging, hands-on instruction designed to be accessible to students with dyslexia</li>
          <li><strong>Extracurricular Activities:</strong> Art, music, and physical education to explore interests and develop talents</li>
          <li><strong>Character Development:</strong> Integrated throughout the school day to build well-rounded students</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <strong>Beyond Remediation:</strong> We don't just help students catch up—we help them excel in all areas
          of academic and personal growth.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="program-card pillar-3">
        <div class="icon-container heart">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
            <path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h2>Pillar 3: A Culture of Character and Faith</h2>
        <p>
          The American Literacy Institute is a faith-friendly school that welcomes families of all backgrounds.
          Our culture is built on a foundation of traditional values, including honesty, integrity, compassion,
          and respect.
        </p>
        <h3>Character Education Focus:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Traditional Values:</strong> Honesty, integrity, compassion, and respect integrated into all aspects of school life</li>
          <li><strong>Service Learning:</strong> Opportunities for students to put their values into action through community outreach</li>
          <li><strong>Leadership Development:</strong> Building not just great students, but great citizens and leaders</li>
          <li><strong>Faith-Friendly Environment:</strong> Welcoming to families of all backgrounds while supporting spiritual development</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <strong>Our Goal:</strong> To develop students who will make a positive impact on the world through both
          their academic excellence and their character.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Get Started?</h2>
      <p>Contact us to learn more about our programs and how to enroll.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Us</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-color) 0%, var(--secondary-color) 100%);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-header p {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .intro {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    background-color: var(--white);
  }

  .intro-text {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: var(--text-color);
  }

  .programs {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .program-card {
    background-color: var(--white);
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 3px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
  }

  .program-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
  }

  .icon-container {
    width: 80px;
    height: 80px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 16px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .icon-container svg {
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    color: var(--white);
  }

  .icon-container.books {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e5a8e, #2a3959);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(30, 90, 142, 0.3);
  }

  .icon-container.target {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #c9a961, #8b7355);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.3);
  }

  .icon-container.heart {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b4513, #6b3410);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(139, 69, 19, 0.3);
  }

  .program-card h2 {
    color: var(--primary-color);
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .program-card p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .program-card h3 {
    color: var(--secondary-color);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .program-card ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .program-card li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .program-card li::before {
    content: "✓";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--secondary-color);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .highlight-box {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--secondary-color) 0%, var(--primary-color) 100%);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .highlight-box strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cta {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--secondary-color) 0%, var(--primary-color) 100%);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cta p {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 1rem 3rem;
    background-color: var(--white);
    color: var(--primary-color);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .program-card h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .cta h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
